description:
Origin

Rosie is a young girl from 1883. She lived with her father in Reyes. One day, while visited the new-built church with her father, the town of Reyes was attacked by the Plague Doctor. Running away from him, he followed her to the riverbed, where he drowned her. Refusing to let go of her body, she returned as a ghost. Years later, she befriended Bee Burton in the sewers, in which he was thrown by his school bully. She later rescued Bee from the same bully by throwing bookcases on him.

Powers & Abilities

Rosie can pull objects and persons into a place between life and death. She calls the place the Betweens.

deck: A former member of HYDRA.
description:
Early Life

Robbie Dean Tomlin had a tough life, his parents struggled by in constant debt and unemployment, plus domestic violence, leaving him unattended. He grew up in front of a TV. With low grades in high school and inability to pay for university, he turned to stealing cars in order to pay rent. However, he got himself caught.

While imprisoned, Robbie fell in with a gang of Neo-Nazis in order to survive in jail. Once he was released, his probation office got him a retail job, but the ensuing financial crisis caused him to lose his job. His life spiraled out of control, Robbie turned to drugs, and even he found a lover, she died due to drug addiction. After that, he struggled to get clean, starting with 12-step programs. He eventually fell off the wagon when his old cellmate invited him to the meeting of an orator who promised to make the country great again.

HYDRA

The speaker of the meeting was none of ther than the Red Skull, whose speech convinced Robbie and all other assistants to join HYDRA, enchanted by a sense of belonging. While he supported Hydra, Robbie became reluctant after witnessing fellow members brutalize and kill an old black man just for the color of his skin.

He was later enlisted to a mission as a suicide bomber. Robbie and other Hydra operatives hijacked a train and directed it to Penn Station. A S.H.I.E.L.D. hacker managed to take control of the train, rerouting it away from the station and detaching it from the cockpit where Robbie was. After subduing the other Hydra operatives, Captain America tried to reach out to Robbie, but the young man detonated his explosive vest, killing himself and destroying part of the train.
name: Robbie Dean Tomlin

deck: Henry Clover is a metahuman and crimefighter. A new protector of Gotham City. He idolized the Batman and desired to help people and fight crime like him. He is a brother to Gotham Girl (Claire Clover) and together with Batman they fight crime in Gotham City. They gained superhuman powers which drained their life force when they used them.
description:
Origin

Hank Clover Jr. was an ordinary boy living in Gotham with his sister Claire Clover (Gotham Girl). One day, as he and his parents were walking down Park Row (now known as Crime Alley), they were approached by an armed mugger who attempted to rob them at gunpoint. However, Batman intervened and knocked the mugger unconscious. Batman inspired him and he desired to fight crime like him. After the encounter, Hank was enamored with Batman, and he wanted to help people like the Batman. Along with his sister, they spent time training, reading and learning all the skills they needed to fight crime. The duo went overseas and did charity work in dangerous places. He and his sister somehow purchased powers that drained their life force when they used them. Together they fight crime in Gotham with Batman.

Powers and Abilities

Adaptive Powers

His powers adjust according to who he's fighting. He becomes stronger and faster at the cost of his life.

Super Strength

Super Speed/Reflexes

Super Hearing

Ultra Vision

Flight

Super Stamina

Invulnerability

Weaknesses

Over Usage of powers / Power Limitation

His powers are inexplicably tied to his life force. The more he uses them, the more his life is reduced. Years of his life will be spent for hours of using his powers. The overuse of powers would lead to his untimely death.

Characteristics / Personal Data

  • Gender: Male
  • Eye Color: Blue
  • Hair Color: Brown
  • Skin Color: White
  • Place of Birth: Gotham
  • Citizenship: American
  • Relatives: Claire Clover (Gotham Girl), Henry Clover Sr, Mrs. Clover
  • Occupation: Super Hero
name: Gotham
